  "details": "A flaw has been found in JD Cloud JDCOS 4.5.1.r4518. This vulnerability affects the function set_iptv_info of the file /jdcap of the component Service Interface. Executing a manipulation of the argument vid can lead to command injection. It is possible to launch the attack remotely. The exploit has been published and may be used. The vendor was contacted early about this disclosure but did not respond in any way.",
